<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><magicdraw><interface classType="Interface" humanType="Interface" icon="index_files/icon_interface_118881143.jpg" id="_10_5_622020d_1132928308179_829231_5176"><UMLClass classType="Class" humanName="Class" humanType="Class" icon="index_files/icon_class_1555793073.jpg" name="Thread" refid="_9_5_f720368_1110473546612_126551_7703"/><documentation humanName="Documentation" mode="standard">Interface for handlers invoked when a &lt;tt&gt;Thread&lt;/tt&gt; abruptly
terminates due to an uncaught exception.
&lt;p&gt;When a thread is about to terminate due to an uncaught exception
the Java Virtual Machine will query the thread for its
&lt;tt&gt;UncaughtExceptionHandler&lt;/tt&gt; using
{@link Thread#getUncaughtExceptionHandler} and will invoke the handler's
&lt;tt&gt;uncaughtException&lt;/tt&gt; method, passing the thread and the
exception as arguments.
If a thread has not had its &lt;tt&gt;UncaughtExceptionHandler&lt;/tt&gt;
explicitly set, then its &lt;tt&gt;ThreadGroup&lt;/tt&gt; object acts as its
&lt;tt&gt;UncaughtExceptionHandler&lt;/tt&gt;. If the &lt;tt&gt;ThreadGroup&lt;/tt&gt; object
has no
special requirements for dealing with the exception, it can forward
the invocation to the {@linkplain #getDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler
default uncaught exception handler}.

@see #setDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler
@see #setUncaughtExceptionHandler
@see ThreadGroup#uncaughtException
@since 1.5
